There's names carved under here. *Quiet.* Did you know that? Probably you didn't. I helped refinish this bench, summer of — '08, I think. The wood was rotting at the joints. Four of us spent a Saturday on it. When we flipped it over to sand the underside, we found them. Names. Initials. Dates going back to the sixties, some of them. Couples who used to come out here to talk. Kids who weren't supposed to be in the courtyard. Somebody who just wanted to leave a mark where nobody preached.

*A small, tired sound.*

